1. cd - change directory

note: just the cd goes into/to the home directoy

2. cd .. - to previous directory

3. mkdir - creates folder/ directory

4. touch example.txt - creates the file with the name we give

5. rm example.txt - removes file

6. rmdir "directory name" - removes the directory

7. pwd - prints the name of current working directory

8. ls - lists the files & folders in the current directory.

//all these is done using the terminal and vim. 
 
